article.description: — Jamaree Bouyea had 20 points as San Francisco beat Towson 71-61 at the Las Vegas Invitational on Thursday night.
article.headline: Bouyea scores 20 to lift San Francisco over Towson 71-61
article.linkText: Bouyea scores 20 to lift San Francisco over Towson 71-61
article.story: PARADISE, Nev. -- — Jamaree Bouyea had 20 points as San Francisco beat Towson 71-61 at the Las Vegas Invitational on Thursday night. Yauhen Massalski had 13 points for San Francisco (7-0), which earned its fifth straight win to start the season. Terry Nolan Jr. had 15 points for the Tigers (3-3). Nicolas Timberlake added 14 points. Cam Holden had 12 points and nine rebounds. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
